Problem Statement:¶

To Predict the Retention Potential levels of customers belonging to a retail company, using their past data of transactions with the company, interactions and value generated to the company.

Business Perspective:¶

In almost any business the rate of customer retentions plays an important role in the growth of any company. The difference between companies that grow and those that don’t is customer churn. The more customers the company can keep and continue to sell to, the more likely it achieves the business goals.

Investment to acquire new customers far exceeds investment on retention. So, it is important for any company to focus on customers retention by identifying and contacting potential customers in different means.

ROI:¶

1.Studies show that atleast 5% increase in customer retention can increase company revenue by 25-95%.

Business Value:¶

  1. Predicting the customers Retention Potential levels gives a clear perspective for the company regarding customers such that different strategies can be derived and used for handling customers of different type.
  2. It helps company to concentrate more on customers who are highly retainable and communicate to them regarding offers or discounts.
  3. Also helps in saving the time and human efforts from contacting the low potential customers who are not going to create any value to tha company.
  4. Depending upon scale of customers a company has, regular prediction of customer retention potential levels and potential rate can help the company to cope up with the needs of the customer.

def inspect_data(data):
    return pd.DataFrame({"Data Type":data.dtypes,"No of Levels":data.apply(lambda x: x.nunique(),axis=0),"% of Unique Levels":data.apply(lambda x: 100*x.nunique()/len(x),axis=0), "Levels":data.apply(lambda x: str(x.unique()),axis=0)}).sort_values("% of Unique Levels", ascending=False)

2.2.4 Transaction Recency:¶

Transaction recency of a customer is the number of days that has happend after his last transaction with the company.

It helps us in identifying the customer activity.

In [40]:
max(transactionsdata_train.DateOfOrder),max(transactionsdata_test.DateOfOrder)
Out[40]:
('2018-01-21', '2018-01-21')

Both transactions data has 21st January 2018 as the last date of transaction, using the same date to calculate the transaction recency.

5 Label Encoding¶

In [218]:
lab_labels=['City', 'OnlineCommunication', 'AutomaticRefill', 'DoorstepDelivery','PreferredDeliveryDay']
def labelencoding(X):
  for i in range(0,len(X.columns)):
      j=X.columns[i]
      if(j in lab_labels):
          le = LabelEncoder()                  # converts the character array to numeric array. Assigns levels to unique labels.
          le.fit(X[j])
          X[j] = le.transform(X[j])
          X[j]=X[j].astype('category')
  return X

Important Feature: NoOfTimesContacted engineered from emails data.

As discussed earlier, for any business interacting with the customers on regular basis is really cruacial to sustain for long time.

  1. Contacting the customers on regular basis by using the model to find the Customer potential levels helps the company to achieve good results in future.
  2. Assuming the train data contains the retention levels collected in human efforts the model helps the company to save time and human efforts.
  3. As from the data we have seen many customers have been contacted only once.
